frameDefinitions: A Figure is located in the interior (the Profiled_region--see Locative_relation frame) of the Ground.
This frame concerns Parts of objects that are defined relative to the center or edge of the object.
As is usual for locative relations, the location of the Figure is specified as being inside a region defined relative to the Ground.
A Survivor manages to avoid being negatively affected, despite encountering a Dangerous_situation.
A Figure is characterized as near the Ground, according to some contextually given scale.
A Trajector is identified as occurring at the same time as some better-known Landmark.
frameExamples: The bookmark <t>inside</t> her book was torn and written on .
She discarded the <t><fex name='Part'>exterior</fex></t> of the walnut.
The number of large galaxies <t>within</t> 5 million light years is three. DNI
Wilderness Survival: Could You <t>Survive</t> the Wild?
She put her shoes <t>under</t> the table .
He tried to take care of that <t>on</t> his last visit .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Figure</fen> is the entity located with respect to the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> is the area that the <fen>Figure</fen> is located in.
The area or zone interior to the <fen>Ground</fen>.  This role excludes <fen>Figure</fen> and is only used in particular constructions such as the following:
The time during which the <fen>Figure</fen> was located in the <fen>Ground</fen>.
This element describes the <fen>Part</fen> of the larger <fen>Whole</fen>.
An undivided entity having all its <fen>Part</fen>s.

The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>, as inside a region measured outward from the <fen>Ground</fen> and of a width specified by <fen>Distance</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location.
This  role identifies the  <fen>Distance</fen> between the <fen>Ground</fen> and the borders of the region within which the <fen>Figure</fen> is located.
The <fen>Survivor</fen> lives through a <fen>Dangerous_situation</fen>.
The <fen>Dangerous_situation</fen> is one in which people are likely or expected to be negatively affected.
The time at which the surviving takes place.
The location where the <fen>Survivor</fen> (primarily) lives during the <fen>Dangerous_situation</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
The entity that occurs at some time.
The event which designates the time at which a trajector occurs.
The period that occurs with respect to some other time.
The period in which a trajector takes place.  This period can be cyclical and, in that case, is interpreted contextually.
The event that occurs at some time.
The entity which designates the time of some trajector.  Note: this role is infrequent or non-existent in English and is included for completeness.
